Method Detail

buildTree

Tree<T> buildTree(java.lang.String treeString)
Build a tree from the given string.

The returned Tree can be used as input to the buildString method to create a String.

The returned Tree will typically hold to the property that treeString.equals(buildString(tree)). In some implementations, the transformation can be lossy such that this property does not hold.

buildString

java.lang.String buildString(Tree<T> tree)
Build a string representing the given tree.

The returned string will always serve as input to the buildTree method to generate a tree.

The returned string will typically hold to the property that tree.equals(buildTree(string)). In some implementations, the transformation can be lossy such that this property does not hold.
